54 55 56 57 58 59  elif c == &#39;2&#39;: k = bytes.fromhex(input(&#34;\nKey : &#34;)) cipher = bytes.fromhex(input(&#34;Ciphertext : &#34;)) flag = decrypt(cipher, k) if b&#34;FwordCTF&#34; in flag: print(f&#34;Well done ! Here is your flag : {FLAG}&#34;)   We can easily bypass this check by providing our own cipher and key, note the condition if b&quot;FwordCTF&quot; in flag:, as long as our decrypted text contains &quot;FwordCTF&quot;, we&rsquo;ll get our flag.
